news.title: MahaRERA to ask builders to report construction quality to aid buyers
news.para: The report will be made available to homebuyers to enable them to make an informed decision. MahaRERAwants to establish processes and standards to minimise likelihood of defects occurring in realty projects.

news.title: Delhi Court issues non-bailable warrants against director of Nivas Promoter
news.para: Metropolitan Magistrate Vinod Joshi, in an order passed on October 11, 2023, issued NBWs against the builder Rahul Chamola who is the Director of Nivas Promoters Pvt Ltd in a case registered against him.

news.title: Sebi to auction nine properties of Orion Industries, Rakhal Bharoti group companies on Nov 20
news.para: ​The nine properties to be auctioned include land parcels located in West Bengal and Jharkhand. The total reserve price of these properties is pegged at around Rs 9 crore, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.

news.title: Gurugram administration holds review meeting with flat owners, residents of Chintels Paradiso
news.para: In the meeting with the residents of D, E, F, G and H towers, the ADC said that in view of the safety of life and property in the society, orders have also been issued by the District Disaster Management Department to vacate the unsafe towers, and it should be vacated.

news.title: Mercedes-Benz's R&D arm renews 5.42 lakh sq ft office lease in Bengaluru
news.para: The R&D centre of the German automaker leased the space at Embassy Crest in Whitefield from Embassy Property Developments for 60 months with a 5% escalation every year.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers sales value up 64% year-on-year in H1 FY24
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers' sales volumes at 1.91 million sq ft improved by 63% in H1 FY24 as against 1.17 million sq ft in H1 FY23. Its collections stood at Rs 985 crore in H1 FY24, up 12% year-on-year from 878 crore in H1 FY23.

news.title: Government should incentivize real estate industry: G. Hari Babu, president, NAREDCO
news.para: "Government is the biggest beneficiary of the real estate industry's growth. If we are expecting 20% of the gross domestic product (GDP) from the construction industry by 2047 then real estate needs to be incentivized," said Hari Babu, president, NAREDCO

news.title: Construction equipment revenue to grow 14-15% this fiscal: Crisil
news.para: In volume terms, the construction equipment sector should see all-time high sales of ~1.2 lakh units this fiscal, compared with ~1.1 lakh units last fiscal, according to Crisil Ratings.

news.title: UP-RERA imposes penalty on five promoters in violation of advertisement and promotion rules
news.para: According to the Pramod Kumar Upadhyay, secretary, UP-RERA, "the amount of penalty being imposed is only a token. As per the provisions of the RERA Act, this penalty could be up to 5 percent of the project cost but authority considered the conditions and imposed the penalty."

news.title: Lokayukta pushes Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to check delays in issuing building permissions
news.para: Many people planning to build their house are blaming HDMC for the inordinate delay in issuing building permission (building licence) as they have been running from pillar to post for this document.

news.title: Mohali development body sites' e-auction from October 15
news.para: Rajiv Kumar Gupta, chief administrator, Greater Mohali Area Development Authority, said the authority has decided to e-auction sites for group housing and schools, and commercial plots besides SCOs/SCFs and booths.

news.title: Poll code casts shadow on property registrations in Telangana
news.para: Senior officials said that a majority of real estate developers, property buyers and those looking for investments will wait till the polls are over.

news.title: ED raids on sand quarries affect supply, prices; shortage hits construction sector
news.para: ED officials have been visiting sand quarry sites across the state to investigate if sand excavated from river beds is being sold illegally, causing a huge loss to the government.

news.title: NGT directs UP to file response on plea questioning exemption from environmental clearance to brick kilns
news.para: This circular was questioned on the grounds of not being compliant with the Supreme Court's directions mandating Environment Impact Assessment clearance from the Union Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh plans to make building foundation checks a must
news.para: For high-risk buildings, especially residential, commercial, industrial, real estate and institutional projects, the geological investigation report as well as the detailed structural design report as per BIS codes is being made mandatory at the time of approval.

news.title: Unsystematic disposal of construction debris by builders irks Nashik civic chief
news.para: During a meeting with the civic body’s Godavari pollution prevention cell, Karanjkar told civic officials to start acting against erring builders and private parties found disposing waste in a haphazard manner.

news.title: KPMG hit with $26 million fine for 'textbook failure' in Carillion audits
news.para: The collapse of Carillion, a major government contractor building hospitals and other infrastructure, in January 2018, along with the collapse of retailer BHS two years earlier, led to three government-backed reviews of auditing markets and standards.

news.title: Mumbai: About 4,700 government employees in Bandra quarters to get ownership flats
news.para: On Wednesday, Shinde had presided over a meeting to discuss the redevelopment of the government colony. At the meeting, Shinde had directed officials to ascertain the development potential of the slum area and submit a detailed redevelopment plan.

news.title: Mumbai: Borivli CHS, developer sent to arbitrator over transit rent dispute
news.para: Om Satyam Niwas CHS, a society in Borivli (West) with 26 flat owners and eight shop owners, went to court last year invoking the arbitration clause in the redevelopment agreement.

news.title: Mumbai: Highstreet Paramvir Developers failed to give information sought for audit
news.para: “During the course of the audit, the auditors had multiple follow-up visits, sent emails and held multiple rounds of discussion, requesting the data required for audit, but the information was not provided for review,” said a senior official.
